{{No footnotes|date=June 2011}}

[[Image:Banana tree paper.jpg|thumb|Banana plant paper.]]'''Banana paper''' is used in two different senses: one refers to a [[paper]] made from the [[Bark (botany)|bark]] of the [[banana]] plant and which is mainly used for artistic purposes; the other to paper made from banana fiber obtained, through an industrial process, from stems and the non-utilizable fruits. This paper can be either hand or machine made.

The [[banana industry|banana agricultural industry]] processes {{convert|42|e6t}} of bananas every year (with {{convert|20000|sqkm}} planted).{{where?|date=June 2011}}{{Citation needed|date=October 2007}} As a result of pulling apart the banana bunches from the main stem, there are leftover stems which contain 5% of fiber useful for the manufacture of paper.{{Citation needed|date=October 2007}}

